%20case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Google%20logo%20is%20seen%20at%20the%20company's%20headquarters%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California%2C%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6235cd6f927f4a001886ad43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Google%20logo%20is%20seen%20at%20the%20company's%20headquarters%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California.%3Cp%3EMarcio%20Jose%20Sanchez%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20judge%20has%20determined%20penalties%20against%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20address%20its%20illegal%20online%20search%20monopoly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20judge%20won't%20force%20Google%20to%20sell%20off%20its%20Chrome%20browser%2C%20as%20the%20DOJ%20requested.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20tech%20company%20can%20no%20longer%20have%20exclusive%20search%20deals%2C%20the%20judge%20ruled.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20on%20Tuesday%20spared%20Google%20from%20a%20breakup%20after%20ruling%20that%20the%20tech%20company's%20online%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-violated-antitrust-law-to-keep-search-monopoly-judge-rules-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esearch%20business%20is%20a%20monopoly%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Judge%20Amit%20Mehta%2C%20in%20a%20230-page%20ruling%2C%20barred%20Google%20from%20having%20exclusive%20contracts%20for%20its%20Google%20Search%2C%20Chrome%2C%20Google%20Assistant%2C%20and%20Gemini%20app%20products%20as%20part%20of%20his%20remedy%20to%20the%20more%20than%20%242%20trillion%20company's%20monopoly%20in%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20ruling%20fell%20short%20of%20some%20of%20the%20most%20contentious%20demands%20from%20the%20US%20government.%20The%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20federal%20judge%20said%20Google%20would%20not%20have%20sell%20off%20its%20Chrome%20browser%20or%20Android%20operating%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlaintiffs%20overreached%20in%20seeking%20forced%20divestiture%20of%20these%20key%20assets%2C%20which%20Google%20did%20not%20use%20to%20effect%20any%20illegal%20restraints%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehta%20wrote%20in%20the%20Tuesday%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShares%20for%20Alphabet%2C%20Google's%20parent%20company%2C%20jumped%20more%20than%206%25%20in%20after-hours%20trading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Mehta%20ordered%20Google%20to%20end%20its%20exclusive%20search%20engine%20deals%2C%20the%20judge%20said%20Google%20could%20still%20strike%20deals%20to%20make%20its%20search%20engine%2C%20Chrome%20browser%2C%20and%20generative%20AI%20products%20the%20default%20choice%20on%20other%20platforms%2C%20like%20on%20smartphones%20and%20internet%20browsers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCutting%20off%20payments%20from%20Google%20almost%20certainly%20will%20impose%20substantial%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20crippling%20%E2%80%94%20downstream%20harms%20to%20distribution%20partners%2C%20related%20markets%2C%20and%20consumers%2C%20which%20counsels%20against%20a%20broad%20payment%20ban%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehta%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Mehta%20ruled%20that%20Google%20share%20search%20index%20and%20user-interaction%20data%20with%20certain%20competitors%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeny%20Google%20the%20fruits%20of%20its%20exclusionary%20acts%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20said%20it%20will%20have%20to%20share%20less%20information%20than%20the%20Justice%20Department%20requested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20order%2C%20Mehta%20remarked%20that%20while%20Google%20remains%20the%20dominant%20player%20in%20online%20search%2C%20the%20legal%20landscape%20shifted%20during%20the%20case%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20general%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20said%20he%20crafted%20the%20remedies%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20healthy%20dose%20of%20humility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20the%20typical%20case%20where%20the%20court's%20job%20is%20to%20resolve%20a%20dispute%20based%20on%20historic%20facts%2C%20here%20the%20court%20is%20asked%20to%20gaze%20into%20a%20crystal%20ball%20and%20look%20to%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehta%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BNot%20exactly%20a%20judge's%20forte.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20decision%20to%20make%20Google%20Search%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20Chrome%2C%20not%20its%20ownership%20of%20the%20browser%2C%20contributed%20to%20its%20monopoly%20power%2C%20Mehta%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForcing%20Google%20to%20sell%20off%20Chrome%20after%20it%20had%20invested%20billions%20of%20dollars%20into%20building%20the%20browser%20would%20be%20the%20wrong%20remedy%20and%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20messy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote%20in%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChrome%20does%20not%20run%20as%20a%20standalone%20business.%20At%20the%20most%20basic%20level%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20Google%20for%20a%20host%20of%20administrative%20functions%2C%20such%20as%20finance%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20human%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20ruled%20the%20order%20will%20remain%20in%20effect%20for%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20can%20be%20paused%20during%20the%20appeals%20process%2C%20which%20could%20drag%20on%20for%20years.%20Google%20previously%20vowed%20to%20appeal%20Mehta's%20original%20ruling%20deeming%20the%20tech%20giant%20a%20monopolist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20the%20DOJ%20didn't%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20ruling%20last%20year%20following%20a%2010-week%20non-jury%20trial%20in%202023%2C%20Mehta%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-antitrust-case-chrome-android-sale-monopoly-doj-remedy-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20violated%20US%20antitrust%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20maintaining%20a%20monopoly%20with%20its%20online%20search%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20is%20a%20monopolist%2C%20and%20it%20has%20acted%20as%20one%20to%20maintain%20its%20monopoly%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehta%20wrote%20in%20the%20ruling%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20showdown%20pitting%20the%20tech%20behemoth%20against%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20and%20a%20coalition%20of%20states%20sparked%20the%20biggest%20monopoly%20ruling%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-plans-major-update-visual-studio-coding-service-ai-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20faced%20a%20potential%20breakup%20nearly%2030%20years%20ago.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%202000%20ordered%20Microsoft%20to%20be%20split%20up%2C%20but%20the%20ruling%20was%20later%20reversed%20on%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20its%20proposed%20remedies%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20Google%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20had%20asked%20Mehta%20to%20force%20Google%20to%20sell%20off%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-sell-chrome-search-winners-losers-doj-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChrome%3C%2Fa%3E%20web%20browser%2C%20end%20its%20exclusive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-billion-dollar-deal-apple-at-risk-monopoly-search-case-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emultibillion-dollar%20deals%20with%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mozilla%2C%20Samsung%2C%20and%20others%20to%20make%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20web%20browsers%20and%20smartphones%2C%20and%20share%20search%20data%20with%20rivals.%20Chrome%20is%20the%20world's%20most%20popular%20web%20browser.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20wanted%20the%20court%20to%20force%20Google%20to%20break%20off%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busine